The paper involves the application of machine learning techniques (neural network) to urban traffic analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the estimation of noise strength parameter, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the use of clustering analysis, which falls under the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). The paper also involves the use of GPS-based traffic data, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of history matching method, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
